65
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,350
Do you see it?

66
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:38,560
If I take the first row
times the first column,

67
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,670
what do I get?

68
00:04:40,670 --> 00:04:42,180
A one.

69
00:04:42,180 --> 00:04:45,070
If I take the first row
times the second column,

70
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:46,830
what do I get?

71
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:47,780
Zero.

72
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:49,670
That's the orthogonality.

73
00:04:49,670 --> 00:04:52,960
The first row times the
last column is zero.

74
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:56,130
And so I'm getting
ones on the diagonal

75
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:59,120
